page.title: 07A walk near Holbeach Hurn.
page.content: One Monday afternoon when the sun was shining we decided to go for a walk to look at what was growing in the fields and hedgerows.To get to the edge of our block we had to walk about a mile up the road.When we got there we could see that most of the fields had vegetable crops in them. In other parts of the block it was either cereal or flowers.We looked at wild flowers and saw dandelion,field poppy,buttercup,comfrey,cow parsley (known here as kek),white dead nettle,stinging nettle,clover,agrimony,groundsel and wild chamomile.We also saw and identified 13 types of grass.There were more that we could not identify.We saw quite a few butterflies.Philip identified the common British Blue and a Skipper.
